WHEN RECORDED RETURN TO:
ENT 68439 : 2014 PG 1 of 1
Jeffery Smith
Utah County Recorder
2014 Sep 24 04:40 PM FEE 10.00 BY EO
RECORDED FOR Olsen Skoubye & Nielson LLC
ELECTRONICALLY RECORDED
CALIFORNIA WHOLESALE MATERIAL SUPPLY, LLC d/b/a BUILDING SPECIALTIES
82 EAST 3450 NORTH
SPANISH FORK, UTAH 84660
(801) 798-8615
NOTICE OF MECHANIC'S LIEN
CALIFORNIA WHOLESALE MATERIAL SUPPLY, LLC d/b/a BUILDING SPECIALTIES, 82 EAST 3450
NORTH, SPANISH FORK, UTAH 84660, (801) 798-8615, lien claimant, through it's limited recording agent, Lien
Utah LLC dba Financial Management Services, hereby holds and claims a mechanic's lien, pursuant to Section 38-
1a-1 et. seq. Utah Code Annotated 1953, as amended, upon the property and improvements owned or reputed to be
owned by UNIVERSITY SQUARE ASSOCIATES LTD AND UNIVERSITY SQUARE ASSOCIATES and located at
approximately 130 E UNIVERSITY PARKWAY, ALSO LISTED WITH THE UTAH COUNTY RECORDER AS 148 E.
UNIVERSITY PARKWAY, 158 E. UNIVERSITY PARKWAY, 168 E. UNIVERSITY PARKWAY, 172 E. UNIVERSITY
PARKWAY, 176 E. UNIVERSITY PARKWAY, 180 E. UNIVERSITY PARKWAY AND 130 EAST 1300 SOUTH,
OREM, UTAH County, Utah and more particularly described as follows:
LEGAL: LOT 1, PLAT C, UNIVERSITY SQUARE
PARCEL 57:014:0001
The lien claimant claims a lien upon the above described property for amounts owing for furnishing
BUILDING MATERIALS in connection with the improvement of said real property. The lien claimant was employed
by HARDCASTLE CONSTRUCTION, INC CORPORATION - PO BOX 617, WASHINGTON, OKLAHOMA 73093 or
furnished the aforesaid services to said individual. There is currently believed to be owed $9,008.35 principal, plus
$120.00 lien filing fees, interest, costs and attorney's fees, which principal amount could change, should additional
credits or charges be discovered. CALIFORNIA WHOLESALE MATERIAL SUPPLY, LLC d/b/a BUILDING
SPECIALTIES furnished the first said BUILDING MATERIALS on JUNE 24, 2014, and the last services were
furnished on JUNE 24, 2014.
NOTICE:
PROTECTION AGAINST LIENS AND CIVIL ACTION. Notice is hereby provided in accordance with Section 38-11-
108 of the Utah Code that under Utah law an "owner" may be protected against liens being maintained against an
"owner- occupied residence" and from other civil action being maintained to recover monies owed for "qualified
services" performed or provided by suppliers and subcontractors as a part of this contract, if either section (1) or (2)
is met: (1)(a) the owner entered into a written contract with an original contractor, a factory built housing retailer, or a
real estate developer; (b) the original contractor was properly licensed or exempt from licensure under Title 58,
Chapter 55, Utah Construction Trades Licensing Act at the time the contract was executed; and(c) the owner paid in
full the contracting entity in accordance with the written contract and any written or oral amendments to the contract;
or (2) the amount of the general contract between the owner and the original contractor totals no more than $5,000."
(3) An owner who can establish compliance with either section (1) or (2) may perfect the owner's protection by
applying for a Certificate of Compliance with the Division of Occupational and Professional Licensing. The
application is available at www.dopl.utah.gov/rirf
Dated 24 September, 2014.
SPECIALTIES, claimant
STATE OF UTAH
: SS ..
COUNTY OF SALT LAKE )
Copy sent to owner of record via Certified Mail # 70111150000040748289
CALIFORNIA WHOLESALE MATERIAL SUPPLY, LLC d/b/a BUILDING
By limited agent, Lien Utah LLC dba Financial Management Services,
By:
lux Frandsen
Lixi Frandsen
On September 24, 2014, being duly subscribed and sworn and appeared before me, Lixi Frandsen, who
said she is an agent authorized to execute liens on behalf of Lien Utah LLC dba Financial Management Services,
and that she executed the above and foregoing instrument as limited agent for the lien claimant and acknowledged
to me that the same is true, IN WITNESS WHEREOF I have herein set my hand and affixed my seal.
Je
NOTARY PUBLIC, Residing in Salt Lake County, UT
Notary Public
DEANNA LINGMANN I
Commission #682617
My Commission Expires
March 7, 2017
State of Utah
------
